definition.value: An alpha-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-D-Gal having beta-configuration at the reducing end anomeric centre.
A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucose at the reducing end having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 4-position.

A polysaccharide derivative composed of repeating disaccharide units, consisting of (1->3)-linked residues of 2,4-diacetamido-2,4-dideoxy-beta-D-quinovose (2,4-diacetamido-2,4,6-trideoxy-beta-D-glucose, bacillosamine) and 2-acetimidoylamino-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucuronic acid.
An optically active form of O(4)-phosphonatotyrosine(2-) having L-configuration.
A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of two alpha-(1->3)-linked N-acetyl-galactosamine units, which are in turn linked beta-(1->3) to an alpha-galactose unit at the reducing end.
An alpha-D-GalpNAc-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc having beta-configuration at the reducing end anomeric centre.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose at the reducing end having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 3-position.
alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc6S in which the configuration at the anomeric centre of the glucosamine residue is beta.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose at the reducing end having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 4-position.

An amino pentasaccharide in which an alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-6-O-sulfo-D-glucosaminyl unit and a D-galactosyl residue are linked respectively beta(1->6) and beta(1->3) to an N-acetyl-D-galactosamine residue.
Any rhamnose having L-configuration. L-rhamnose occurs naturally in many plant glycosides and some gram-negative bacterial lipopolysaccharides.
An L-rhamnose in cyclic pyranose form.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of alpha-L-rhamnose at the reducing end having an alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl moiety attached at the 2-position.
An amino disaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl residue attached at the 2-position.
An amino disaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl residue attached at the 4-position.
A glycosylmannose consisting of D-galactofuranose linked beta(1->2) to D-mannopyranose.
An amino disaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose having an N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl residue attached at the 2-position.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of beta-D-galactose having an alpha-D-glucosyl residue attached at the 2-position.
A glycosylgalactose in which one D-galactofuranosyl residue is linked beta(1->6) to a second D-galactofuranose residue.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of beta-D-galactose having an beta-D-glucosyl residue attached at the 2-position.
A D-glucosyl-D-mannose with the two components joined by an beta-(1->2)-linkage and alpha-cofiguration at the reducing end anomeric centre.
An alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)-D-Manp having alpha-configuration at the reducing end anomeric centre.
The methyl glycoside of the disaccharide beta-D-galactofuranosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-mannose.
The methyl glycoside of the disaccharide beta-D-galactofuranosyl-(1->3)-alpha-D-mannose.
A glycoside that is the n-propyl glycoside of beta-D-mannopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-mannopyranosyl-(1->2)-2-thio-beta-D-mannopyranose.
A glycohexaosylceramide having alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycohexaosyl component.
An alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-D-Glcp having beta-configuration at the reducing end anomeric centre.
A glycoside that is the n-propyl glycoside of beta-D-mannopyranosyl-(1->2)-2-thio-beta-D-mannopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-mannopyranose.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-glucose at the reducing end having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 4-position.
A seven-membered oligopeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, Ala, Met, Cys(Acm), Ser and Leu-NH2 residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic six-membered oligopeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, Ala, Odapdc, Ser and Leu-NH2 residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic tetrapeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, MeAla and Haic-NHCH(CH2OH)2 residues coupled in sequence.
A synthetic seven-membered oligopeptide comprising Ac-Cha, Arg, MePhg, Met, Ala, Ser and tLeu-NH2 residues coupled in sequence.
A sialotetraosylceramide having alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialotetraosyl component.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by removal of the proton from the phosphate group of propanoyl-AMP; major species at pH 7.3
Dianion of UDP-N-acetyl-6-deoxy-beta-L-talosamine arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A branched trisaccharide consisting of beta-D-mannose having beta-D-xylosyl and alpha-D-mannosyl residues attached at the 2- and 6-positions respectively.

A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a branched nonasaccharide made up from one sialyl residue, two galactose residues, one L-fucose residue, one N-acetylglucosamine residue and one glucose residue, which at the reducing end is attached to the ceramide portion via a beta-linkage.
A doubly-charged nucleotide-sugar oxoanion arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups of UDP-2-acetamido-2,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-xylo-hex-4-ulose; major species at pH 7.3.
A branched tetrasaccharide consisting of beta-D-mannose having two alpha-D-mannosyl residues attached at the 3- and 6-positions as well as a beta-D-xylosyl residue at the 2-position.
A doubly-charged nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained via deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of UDP-2-acetamido-2,6-dideoxy-beta-L-lyxo-hex-4-ulose; major species at pH 7.3.
A branched amino trisaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine having alpha-L-fucosyl and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residues attached at positions 3 and 4 respectively.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine having two alpha-L-fucosyl residues at the 3- and 6-positions as well as an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue at the 4-position.

A ten-membered branched glucosamine oligosaccharide consisting of two alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[beta-D-Glc-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal units connected via a beta-(1->4) linkage from the galactose to the glucose.

A ten-membered branched glucosamine oligosaccharide consisting of two alpha-Neu5Pr-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[beta-D-Glc-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal units connected via a beta-(1->4) linkage from the galactose to the glucose.
A myo-inositol monophosphate in which the phosphate group is located at the 2-position.
A carboxylic ester-lactam secreted by Mycobacterium tuberculosis which is lipid-soluble and acts as an antigen.

A fifteen-membered glycopeptide comprising glycyl, isoleucyl, alanyl, glycyl, phenylalanyl, (5R)-5-(beta-D-galactopyranosyloxy)lysyl, glycyl. alpha-glutamyl, glutaminyl, glycyl, prolyl, lysyl, glycyl, alpha-glutamyl and threonine residues coupled in sequence.

A fifteen-membered glycopeptide comprising glycyl, isoleucyl, alanyl, glycyl, 4-fluorophenylalanyl, (5R)-5-(beta-D-galactopyranosyloxy)lysyl, glycyl. alpha-glutamyl, glutaminyl, glycyl, prolyl, lysyl, glycyl, alpha-glutamyl and threonine residues coupled in sequence.

A fifteen-membered glycopeptide comprising glycyl, isoleucyl, alanyl, glycyl, tyrosyl, (5R)-5-(beta-D-galactopyranosyloxy)lysyl, glycyl. alpha-glutamyl, glutaminyl, glycyl, prolyl, lysyl, glycyl, alpha-glutamyl and threonine residues coupled in sequence.
